        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/131922-mark-monday?shelf=scifi-modern">scifi-modern</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/131922-mark-monday?shelf=into-the-past">into-the-past</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer534714072" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8732080542706063455">and what exactly was the point of this nearly 600-page novel? that people can be incredibly annoying and repetitious? that the Black Death kills? i can&apos;t believe i wasted so many hours reading this flabby, irritating nonsense. i could have been spending time with friends or exercising or taking naps. or reading another book. the entire thing is a monument to wasted time - my time and the characters&apos; time and the 5 years of time it took to write this extravagantly dreary ode to pointlessness.<br/><br/>real</span>
  <span id="freeText8732080542706063455" style="display:none">and what exactly was the point of this nearly 600-page novel? that people can be incredibly annoying and repetitious? that the Black Death kills? i can't believe i wasted so many hours reading this flabby, irritating nonsense. i could have been spending time with friends or exercising or taking naps. or reading another book. the entire thing is a monument to wasted time - my time and the characters' time and the 5 years of time it took to write this extravagantly dreary ode to pointlessness.<br><br>real review to come, maybe, if i can summon up the energy. but for now, one word can describe my thoughts on this travesty:<br><br><a href="http://s181.beta.photobucket.com/user/markmonday/media/lame-gif_zps63e2ac0e.gif.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">
