<div id="review_816729083" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/816729083" />
    <a title="Kaethe Douglas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1072582-kaethe-douglas"><img alt="Kaethe Douglas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1573927565p2/1072582.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/816729083?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaethe Douglas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaethe Douglas" href="/user/show/1072582-kaethe-douglas">Kaethe Douglas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=strong-smart-female-protagonist">strong-smart-female-protagonist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=feminism">feminism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=plagues">plagues</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=scifi">scifi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=time-travel">time-travel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=beloved">beloved</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=uk">uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1072582-kaethe-douglas?shelf=format-ebooks">format-ebooks</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer816729083" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1355479569664785052">1995<br/><br/>***<br/>5/28/2000 <br/>I was waiting to pick up a prescription, and I finished the book I was reading. I broke out my Kindle, thinking I&apos;d read something on it, at least one of the samples. But what I really wanted to read was <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7519231.All_Clear__All_Clear___2_' title='All Clear (All Clear, #2) by Connie Willis' rel='nofollow noopener'>All Clear</a>. But then I thought I&apos;d better reread <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6506307.Blackout__All_Clear___1_' title='Blackout (All Clear, #1) by Connie Willis' rel='nofollow noopener'>Blackout</a> since it&apos;s been six months or more. And then, when I started Blackout I saw Colin mentioned from the Doomsday Book, so I downloaded that to start with. So, the two re-reads followed by the new book should keep me busy.<br/><br/>Janu</span>
  <span id="freeText1355479569664785052" style="display:none">1995<br /><br />***<br />5/28/2000 <br />I was waiting to pick up a prescription, and I finished the book I was reading. I broke out my Kindle, thinking I'd read something on it, at least one of the samples. But what I really wanted to read was <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7519231.All_Clear__All_Clear___2_" title="All Clear (All Clear, #2) by Connie Willis" rel="nofollow noopener">All Clear</a>. But then I thought I'd better reread <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6506307.Blackout__All_Clear___1_" title="Blackout (All Clear, #1) by Connie Willis" rel="nofollow noopener">Blackout</a> since it's been six months or more. And then, when I started Blackout I saw Colin mentioned from the Doomsday Book, so I downloaded that to start with. So, the two re-reads followed by the new book should keep me busy.<br /><br />January 22 2011 <br /><br />Such a sad and wonderful book.<br /><br />***<br /><br />11 May 2021<br /><br />I've been wanting to reread but also, I've been afraid. I suppose now that the immediate family are all fully vaccinated the fear isn't as great, but it's not over yet. There's still plenty of horror left.<br /><br />***<br /><br />15 May 2021<br /><br />Heartbreaking and yet hopeful.<br /><br />Willis manages to capture how horrible the experience is for some, while others are unaffected. The confusion, the contradictory advice, the protesters, the failur es and shortages (toilet paper, protective equipment, drugs) the finger-pointing, blaming, and incorrect and disparaging attributions and names, the many struggling through, the desperate and deadly urge to come together for comfort. About the only thing she didn't get was immunization guilt. Stupid bodies being stupidly vulnerable to everything.<br /><br />Carrying on is both a distraction from and the only meaningful goal sometimes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1355479569664785052" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


